views.text:
Millions of home cooks and culinary professionals swear by gas stoves. The idea of a wok stir fry or cooking the perfect tortilla over electric coils is utterly unthinkable. But more data is beginning to emerge highlighting the real dangers of burning natural gas indoors. The long-term consequences can be deadly.

L.A. Times environmental reporter Tony Briscoe wrote about a new Stanford study and joined Lisa McRee with the details.
Cynthia Nixon on pulling double duty for HBO, Max and Lulu Wang on her leap to TV
